  <span id="freeText515661987471531826" style="display:none">Beautiful, broadly painted chronicle of the history of the city of Visegerad, and by extension Bosnia and Serbia. The bridge that was built in the 16th century functions as a spindle around which all kinds of individual and collective stories are woven. Main thematic background: the problematic coexistence of Muslims, Christians and Jews, and the puny vicissitudes of individual life against the unflappable permanence of structures like a bridge. The chapter about the arrival of the Austrians illustrates nicely the advent of modernity and the adjustment problems that this created.<br />(rating 3.5 stars)</span>
