<div id="review_3453320243" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3453320243" />
    <a title="Kiran Bhat" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/81560301-kiran-bhat"><img alt="Kiran Bhat" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1525335374p2/81560301.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3453320243?book_show_action=true">Jul 20, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kiran Bhat" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kiran Bhat" href="/user/show/81560301-kiran-bhat">Kiran Bhat</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3453320243" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4002906887192980058">One of the most under-rated classics of world literature. The Bridge on the Drina is a book of great delirium, as well as a book of great magic and wonder. It&apos;s hard not to read the book as an allegory of the tragic history that would later befall Bosnia. Somehow, Andric was able to capture the decline of nations and communities, and to do so with almost mythical pause. </span>
  <span id="freeText4002906887192980058" style="display:none">One of the most under-rated classics of world literature. The Bridge on the Drina is a book of great delirium, as well as a book of great magic and wonder. It's hard not to read the book as an allegory of the tragic history that would later befall Bosnia. Somehow, Andric was able to capture the decline of nations and communities, and to do so with almost mythical pause. </span>
